    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.0-dev-395+g3098064f3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nYes, see vim/vim#11628\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.0.10-arch2-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n1. Create a config file (called 'init_winscrolled-incsearch.vim' in this example') with the following content:\r\n```vim\r\nlet g:n = 0\r\nau WinScrolled * let g:n = g:n + 1\r\nset incsearch\r\n```\r\n2. `nvim -u init_winscrolled-incsearch.vim`\r\n3. `:help`\r\n4. `:echo g:n` and remember its value (should be 1).\r\n5. Press `/` and type `within`. During that it should scroll window twice: at `wit` and `withi`.\r\n6. Type `<C-c>` to abort search. It should scroll back to initial position.\r\n7. `:echo g:n` still shows the same value as before, however, it should be increased by 3.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`WinScrolled` is triggered on every window scroll.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`WinScrolled` is not triggered during initial phase of `incsearch`.\r\n\r\n**Note**: I first opened an issue in Vim (vim/vim#11628), but it seems that it won't get resolved there. So I decided to open it here now, as my use case is actually Neovim based.",
